        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 2 at 3:38PM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sidman, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blue Knob State Park, Martinsburg, Blue Knob Ski Resort, Queen,
Roaring Spring, Ski Gap, Woodbury, Saxton, Hollidaysburg, East
Freedom, Altoona-Blair County Airport, Duncansville, Claysburg,
Newry, and Royer.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
